        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 2:43PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Blooming Grove to near
Kennedy. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fayette, Millport, Kennedy, Belk, Ashcraft Corner, Bankston,
Crossville, Cody, Stone Wall, Richard Arthur Field, Fayette County
Public Lake, Bevill State College Fayette, and Hubbertville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
